# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This repository intentionally contains NO secrets.
#
# The OpenAI API key is NEVER stored here, in docker-compose.yml,
# or in any Docker image. You add it ONCE inside the Flowise UI:
#     Flowise → Credentials → Add Credential → OpenAI
# Flowise encrypts it into the local `flowise_data` volume only.
#
# Flowise's chatflow JSON export also strips all credentials, so the
# exported flow committed to this repo is safe to share publicly.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OPTIONAL: pin Flowise's credential-encryption key so saved credentials
# survive a full volume reset. Leave unset to let Flowise auto-generate it.
# (If you set this, copy this file to `.env` — which is gitignored.)
# FLOWISE_SECRETKEY_OVERWRITE=
